(70, 'Speaker Dr Shirin urges journos for improving Bangladesh-India ties', 1, 'Jatiya Sangsad Speaker Dr Shirin Sharmin Chaudhury has called upon journalists of Bangladesh and India to play a constructive role in improving Bangladesh-India relationship.\nDr Shirin Sharmin Chaudhury was addressing the inaugural of a seminar titled \"Role of Bangladesh-India Relations: Challenges and Prospects\" organised by the National Press Club at its auditorium today.\nThe two countries signed a number of agreements and MoUs on social, economic, maritime and environmental cooperation, Shirin Sharmin said.\nThough the two countries addressed many problems, some issues like water sharing are still not progressing much.\nBangladesh faces immense problems due to flooding that the upper riparian countries India, Nepal or Bhutan do not face, he said.', '2022-10-20 08:05:06', NULL, 1, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/news/bangladesh/news/speaker-dr-shirin-sharmin-urges-journos-improving-bangladesh-india-relationship-3147656', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicimages202210201666251596-unb_newswire.jpg'),
(71, 'DMP commissioner Shafiqul Islam to retire Oct 30', 1, 'Dhaka Metropolitan Police (DMP) Commissioner Md Shafiqul Islam is going to retire from government services on October 30, 2022.\nA notification of the Public Security Division of the Ministry of Home Affairs issued today (October 20, 2022) confirmed the matter.\nAccording to the notification, post-retirement leave from October 30, 2022 to October 29, 2023 has been granted in favour of retired Commissioner of Police (Additional IGP, Grade-1) Md Shafiqul Islam by notification dated 28 October 2021 of the Ministry of Public Administration.\nHe will also be entitled to retirement and post-retirement leave benefits as per the rules, the notification said.\nMd Shafiqul Islam took over as the Commissioner of Dhaka Metropolitan Police on September 7, 2019.', '2022-10-20 08:05:33', NULL, 1, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/news/bangladesh/news/dmp-commissioner-shafiqul-islam-retire-oct-30-3147646', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicimages20221020dmp_chief_4.jpg'),
(72, 'Ghorashal Power Station’s unit-5 resumes operation after 2 weeks of grid failure', 1, 'After two weeks of remaining out of order, the 210 MW capacity unit-5 of Ghorashal Power Station has resumed operation.\nExcept unit-5, almost all other units of the power station resumed operation the same day.\nAs a result, Dhaka city and adjoining areas were getting relatively less power supply from Ghorashal.\nPower generation resumption from unit-5 will help improve the electricity supply situation in Dhaka and surrounding areas, said another BPDB official.\nDhaka city and adjoining areas are still experiencing frequent load shedding due to a huge gap between power supply and demand.', '2022-10-20 08:05:50', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651333/Ghorashal-Power-Station’s-unit5-resumes-operation-after-2-weeks-of-grid-failure', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020power.jpg'),
(73, 'Train services on Dhaka-Mymensingh route suspended', 1, 'Train services on the Dhaka-Mymensingh route have been suspended since Thursday morning, with a crane overturning on the railway track in the Satkhamair area of Gazipur\'s Sreepur upazila.\nHarun-or-Rashid, station master of Sreepur Railway Station, said the crane was brought to Sreepur for carrying out repairs of the railway track in the morning.\n\"Mymensingh-bound ‘Teesta Express’ and a Dhaka-bound commuter train are currently stranded at Sreepur railway station and Kawraide point, respectively,\" he said.\n“Efforts are on to remove the crane from the railway track soon,” he added.', '2022-10-20 08:05:56', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651327/Train-services-on-DhakaMymensingh-route-suspended', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images2022102021HcPeSxnMMGrAm65R0Prr2kHzZRfJh9JJfKGTSr.jpg'),
(74, 'Under-pressure Putin \'doubles down\' with security decree', 1, 'In those regions close to the border with Ukraine, such as Belgorod, Bryansk, Krasnodar and Rostov regions, as well as in annexed Crimea, a \"medium level of response\" has been declared.\nMeasures include boosting security and public order: the decree also envisages restrictions on the movement of traffic, as well as on entry into and exit from these regions.', '2022-10-20 08:06:12', NULL, 1, 'https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-63319100', 'httpsichef.bbci.co.uknews1024branded_newsE048production_127261475_mediaitem127261471.jpg');
