(94, 'Man Utd too good for Tottenham, Liverpool revival rolls on', 0, '\"We had some more really good performances like Liverpool and Arsenal but this was the game from start to the end we were really good,\" said Ten Hag.\nThe Red Devils had 28 shots on goal against a Tottenham side that been beaten only once in their opening 10 league games of the season.\nNunez powered Kostas Tsimikas\' cross into the far corner for the game\'s only goal on 22 minutes.\nAlisson was needed once more to deny Tomas Soucek from point-blank range late on as Liverpool held out.\nThe Saints\' first win in six lifts them up to 14th, but still only two points clear of the bottom three.', '2022-10-20 10:00:38', '2022-10-20 10:01:23', 0, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/post/651316/Man-Utd-too-good-for-Tottenham-Liverpool-revival-rolls-on', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020man.jpg'),
(95, 'ACC okays chargesheet against 9 including 5 ex-NSU trustees', 1, 'The Anti-Corruption Commission (ACC) has approved a charge sheet against nine people including five of the board of trustees of North-South University for laundering about Tk 303.82 crore.\nACC will submit charge-sheet before court soon, said ACC Secretary Mahbub Hossain.\nThe accused former NSU trustees are Azim Uddin Ahmed, chairman of Mutual Group of Companies; Benajir Ahmed, managing director and CEO of Raymond Group of Industries; MA Kashem, chairman of Mutual Group of Industries; Rehana Rahman, MD of Bengal Tradeways Ltd; Mohammed Shajahan, MD of Shah Fatehullah Textile Mills Ltd.\nThe other accused in the charge sheet are Ashaloy Housing and Developers MD Amin Md Hilaly, its chairman Omar Faruk and directors Anwara Begum and Syed AK Haque.', '2022-10-20 10:00:46', NULL, 1, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/news/bangladesh/crime-justice/news/acc-approves-charge-sheet-against-9-including-5-ex-nsu-trustees-3147711', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicfeatureimagesnsu_26.jpg'),
(96, 'bKash offers up to 50% discount on tour packages, hotels & airfares', 4, '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 14px; float: none; padding: 0px 0px 10px; width: auto; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(196, 191, 183); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify;\">By teaming up with some reputed hotels, airlines and tour operators, bKash Limited, the largest mobile financial service provider in the country has been offering its customers up to 50% discount on room rents, air tickets and tour packages on bKash payment. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 14px; float: none; padding: 0px 0px 10px; width: auto; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(196, 191, 183); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify;\">bKash announced the travel scheme in the middle of October aiming to bring happiness and encouragement to its customers amid big savings on travel during country’s peak holiday season beginning from October to December. The offer will last till December 31, 2018.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 14px; float: none; padding: 0px 0px 10px; width: auto; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(196, 191, 183); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify;\">The largest mobile financial service provider in the country launched the discount deal in partnership with Grand Sultan Tea Resort and Golf, Nokkhottrobari Resort &amp; Conference Center, Shaira Garden Hotel and Resort, Hotel The Cox Today, Prassad Paradise Hotel &amp; Resort, Nazimgarh Resort, Ocean Paradise Hotel &amp; Resort and Royal Tulip Sea Pearl Resort &amp; Spa, Travel Zoo Bangladesh, Aoterk Tourism Ltd, ITS Holiday Ltd, Bangladesh Parjatan Corporation, US Bangla Airlines, Regent Airways and Nandan Park. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 14px; float: none; padding: 0px 0px 10px; width: auto; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(196, 191, 183); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify;\">To avail the discount, bKash customers have to make the payment via bKash app or USSD channel *247# while purchasing holiday packages, renting room and buying air tickets from the participating merchants.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 14px; float: none; padding: 0px 0px 10px; width: auto; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(196, 191, 183); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify;\">The details of the offer along with terms and conditions is available at bKash website&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bkash.com/bn/travel_discount\" style=\"color: rgb(238, 50, 132);\">https://www.bkash.com/bn/travel_discount</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;and Facebook page&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/bkashlimited/\" style=\"color: rgb(238, 50, 132);\">https://www.facebook.com/bkashlimited/</a></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 14px; float: none; padding: 0px 0px 10px; width: auto; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(196, 191, 183); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify;\">Launched in 2011, bKash, a joint venture of BRAC Bank, US based Money in Motion, International Finance Corporation of World Bank Group, Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation and China based Ant Financial(Ali Pay) , an affiliate of Alibaba Group offers broad range of mobile financial services to the common people of Bangladesh.</p>', '2022-10-20 10:05:34', NULL, 1, 'bKash-offers-up-to-50%-discount-on-tour-packages,-hotels-&-airfares', 'f99c9e460afc9ae17690fdd0ac6296d1.jpg'),
(97, 'Man Utd too good for Tottenham, Liverpool revival rolls on', 0, '\"We had some more really good performances like Liverpool and Arsenal but this was the game from start to the end we were really good,\" said Ten Hag.\nThe Red Devils had 28 shots on goal against a Tottenham side that been beaten only once in their opening 10 league games of the season.\nNunez powered Kostas Tsimikas\' cross into the far corner for the game\'s only goal on 22 minutes.\nAlisson was needed once more to deny Tomas Soucek from point-blank range late on as Liverpool held out.\nThe Saints\' first win in six lifts them up to 14th, but still only two points clear of the bottom three.', '2022-10-20 10:35:45', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/post/651316/Man-Utd-too-good-for-Tottenham-Liverpool-revival-rolls-on', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020man.jpg'),
(98, 'No good news yet from China on Rohingya repatriation: Momen', 1, 'Foreign Minister Dr AK Abdul Momen today (October 20, 2022) said the Chinese side is yet to come up with any good news on the Rohingya repatriation but they are continuing their efforts to that end.\n\"My key discussion (with Chinese Ambassador to Bangladesh) today focused on Myanmar and the Rohingya issue,\" he told reporters after his meeting with Chinese Ambassador to Bangladesh Li Jiming.\nThe hour-long meeting was held at the State guesthouse Padma while the Foreign Minister briefed the media at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.\n\"That\'s good news but there is no specific date (when repatriation will begin),\" Momen said.\nBrokered by China, Bangladesh and Myanmar signed an agreement for starting repatriation of the Rohingya refugees to Myanmar under a tripartite mechanism, but the process remained stalled.', '2022-10-20 10:35:52', NULL, 1, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/rohingya-influx/news/no-good-news-yet-chinese-side-rohingya-repatriation-momen-3147746', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicmediaapi_images20220828rohingya%20file.jpg'),
(99, 'ACC okays chargesheet against 9 including 5 ex-NSU trustees', 1, 'The Anti-Corruption Commission (ACC) has approved a charge sheet against nine people including five of the board of trustees of North-South University for laundering about Tk 303.82 crore.\nACC will submit charge-sheet before court soon, said ACC Secretary Mahbub Hossain.\nThe accused former NSU trustees are Azim Uddin Ahmed, chairman of Mutual Group of Companies; Benajir Ahmed, managing director and CEO of Raymond Group of Industries; MA Kashem, chairman of Mutual Group of Industries; Rehana Rahman, MD of Bengal Tradeways Ltd; Mohammed Shajahan, MD of Shah Fatehullah Textile Mills Ltd.\nThe other accused in the charge sheet are Ashaloy Housing and Developers MD Amin Md Hilaly, its chairman Omar Faruk and directors Anwara Begum and Syed AK Haque.', '2022-10-20 10:36:18', NULL, 1, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/news/bangladesh/crime-justice/news/acc-approves-charge-sheet-against-9-including-5-ex-nsu-trustees-3147711', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicfeatureimagesnsu_26.jpg'),
(100, 'Dengue infections may drop next month: DGHS', 1, 'Dengue cases are likely to start dropping from early November, said Directorate General of Health Services (DGHS) Director (disease control) Professor Dr Nazmul Islam on Thursday.\nThe year dengue infections have increased due to climate change and lack of awareness among people, he told the reporters at an event organized by National Malaria Eradication and Aedes Transmitted Diseases (ATDS) Control Programme at a city hotel.\nHe also said the hospital authorities have taken all necessary measures to provide treatment to the increasing dengue patients.\n“Deaths from dengue can be reduced significantly if patients consult with doctors in time.”With seven more deaths from dengue confirmed on Wednesday, the official death toll from the disease rose to 106 in this year - the second-highest on record after the 179 deaths recorded in 2019.\nThe total number of cases this year stood at 27,802.', '2022-10-20 10:36:36', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651351/Dengue-infections-may-drop-next-month:-DGHS', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020debgue.PNG'),
(101, 'Media can play role in deepening Bangladesh-India ties: Speaker', 1, 'Jatiya Sangsad Speaker Shirin Sharmin Chaudhury has said the media can play their roles in promoting the activities that can help further deepen the bilateral relations between Bangladesh and India.\nShe urged the journalists of both Bangladesh and India to play constructive role in improving Dhaka-Delhi ties.\nSpeaker Chaudhury said the two countries have addressed many challenges in the past years, including land and maritime boundaries demarcation.\nIndian Journalists’ Union President Geetartha Pathak said Bangladesh and India share common history and culture.\nBangladesh faces immense problems due to flooding that the upper riparian countries India, Nepal or Bhutan do not face, he said.', '2022-10-20 10:36:41', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651347/Media-can-play-role-in-deepening-BangladeshIndia-ties:-Speaker', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020speaker.jpg'),
(102, 'Under-pressure Putin \'doubles down\' with security decree', 1, 'In those regions close to the border with Ukraine, such as Belgorod, Bryansk, Krasnodar and Rostov regions, as well as in annexed Crimea, a \"medium level of response\" has been declared.\nMeasures include boosting security and public order: the decree also envisages restrictions on the movement of traffic, as well as on entry into and exit from these regions.', '2022-10-20 10:36:57', NULL, 1, 'https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-63319100', 'httpsichef.bbci.co.uknews1024branded_newsE048production_127261475_mediaitem127261471.jpg'),
