(104, 'Man held with yaba pills in Savar, case filed', 1, 'Members of Detective Branch (DB) of Police arrested a man with 6,000 yaba pills in Savar last night (October 19, 2022).\nThe arrestee is Jalal Uddin (35) of North Bhashantek area of the capital.\nDB\'s Dhaka District (North) Officer-in-charge Riaz Uddin Ahmed confirmed this to our Savar correspondent.\nBased on secret information, the DB men conducted a drive at a rented house in Savar\'s Kaundia area and arrested Jalal with the pills around 8pm.\nActually, he runs the drug business under the guise of rice business, OC Riaz Uddin said quoting the arrestee.', '2022-10-20 16:34:59', NULL, 1, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/news/bangladesh/crime-justice/news/man-held-yaba-pills-savar-case-filed-3147981', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicimages20221020db.jpg'),
(105, '2 children electrocuted in Habiganj', 1, 'Two children died after being electrocuted at Sultanshi village in Habiganj Sadar upazila this evening (October 20, 2022).\nThey deceased were identified as Shimla Akhter (9), daughter of Abul Latif of Shultanshi village and her cousin Rojina Akhter (7), daughter of Siddique Ali of Abdabkhai village, reports our Moulvibazar correspondent quoting Golam Mortaza, officer-in-charge of Habiganj Sadar Police Station.\nShimla and Rojina were third and second grade students respectively at a local primary school.\nOC Mortaza said the they were playing at the yard of their house this evening.\nLater, locals rescued them and took them to Habiganj Sadar Adhunik Hospital where on-duty doctor Mehdi Hasan declared them dead, informed the OC.', '2022-10-20 16:35:28', NULL, 1, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/news/bangladesh/accidents-fires/news/2-children-electrocuted-habiganj-3147971', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicuploads20210714habiganj.jpg'),
(106, 'Two minor girls electrocuted in Habignaj', 1, 'Two minor girls died after being electrocuted at Sultanshi village in Sadar upazila this afternoon.\nThe deceased were identified as Shimla, 10, hailed from the village, and Rozina, 10.\nThey were cousins.\nThey used to read in class four.\nOfficer-in-Charge of Sadar Thana Golam Mortuza confirmed.', '2022-10-20 16:35:45', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651400/Two-minor-girls-electrocuted-in-Habignaj', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020Electorcution-ds.jpg'),
(107, 'AL is not obstructing BNP rally, says Obaidul Quader', 1, 'Awami League General Secretary Obaidul Quader on Thursday said the government did not make any attempts to thwart the BNP’s anti-government rally, rather extended administrative support.\n\"Neither the government nor the Awami League has ever created any obstacles to holding the rally by BNP, and (we) will never do so,\" he told reporters at Shetu Bhaban in Dhaka.\n\"The transport strike was not there, so why wasn\'t the rally venue full of people in Chattogram?”Quader said that neither the government nor the Awami League is intimidating the upcoming rally in Khulna.\nTransport workers and owners in the southwestern region said they would suspend bus services in Khulna ahead of the BNP rally on Saturday as they are afraid of violence, Quader added.\n“What can the government or Awami League do (in that case)?”In response to the statement by BNP Secretary General Mirza Fakhrul Islam Alamgir that Awami League had created 1/11, Quader said: “Who was in power before 1/11?”Quader said that BNP wanted to destroy the entire election system by making 1.23 crore fake voters.', '2022-10-20 16:35:54', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651396/AL-is-not-obstructing-BNP-rally-says-Obaidul-Quader', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020quader.jpg'),
(108, 'Abolfazl Adinezadeh: Teenage protester shot dead by security forces - sources', 1, 'Recently, he had become increasingly angry about corruption, the death last month of Mahsa Amini - the 22-year-old woman who fell into a coma after being detained by morality police - as well as the footage of other women being beaten and killed in the streets, the sources said.', '2022-10-20 16:36:12', NULL, 1, 'https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-63328086', 'httpsichef.bbci.co.uknews1024branded_newsF68Dproduction_127271136_abolfazl1.jpg'),
(109, 'China anger over death of girl, 14, sent to Covid quarantine', 1, 'The relative said JinJin had been taken to a quarantine centre set up in a local school and placed in a separate building to her father.\nHundreds of other children are being held in such centres across the region - with many separated from their families.', '2022-10-20 16:36:31', NULL, 1, 'https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-63324655', 'httpsichef.bbci.co.uknews1024branded_news18502production_127268599_gettyimages-1385594315.jpg'),
(110, 'It\'s difficult that everyone is slowly leaving us behind: Dilara Zaman reminisces Masum Aziz', 3, 'Ekushey Padak-winning actress, Dilara Zaman is still active in the industry, even at the age of 80.\nDilara Zaman said, \"Even if I want to, I cannot do a lot of acting work due to my age.\nIn response to a question, the five-decade-tenured Dilara Zaman said, \"It is very difficult that everyone is slowly leaving us behind.\nI was also very close to Masum Aziz and he too left us as well.\"\nRegarding the late Masum Aziz, Dilara noted how she had worked in his first directorial series, \"Boro Maa\".', '2022-10-20 16:37:03', '2022-10-20 16:39:22', 0, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/entertainment/tv-film/news/its-difficult-everyone-slowly-leaving-us-behind-dilara-zaman-reminisces-masum-aziz-3147886', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicimages20221020dilara_zaman_1.jpg'),
(111, 'Vidyut, Arjun Rampal, Jacqueline Fernandez to star in extreme-sports film \'Crakk\'', 3, 'Bollywood actors Vidyut Jammwal, Arjun Rampal, and Jacqueline Fernandez are teaming up to work on the upcoming sports-action film, \"Crakk\".\nJammwal will be performing a variety of extreme sports stunts and action sequences in \"Crakk\", which is being touted as India\'s first-ever extreme-sports-action movie.\nHis dedication to perfect action sequences is truly commendable.\"\nJacqueline also shared that she was very impressed by the storyline of \"Crakk\" and immediately wanted to be a part of such a unique film.\nThe shooting of the film has already started in Poland and it is scheduled for release in 2023.', '2022-10-20 16:37:32', '2022-10-20 16:39:12', 0, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/entertainment/tv-film/news/vidyut-arjun-rampal-jacqueline-fernandez-star-extreme-sports-film-crakk-3147876', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicimages20221020untitled_design_22.png'),
(112, 'Chandan Sinha: singer of the decade', 3, 'Choice by audience vote apparently an \'non performing singer\' Chandan Sinha won the crown of the Singer of the Decade.\nVery choosy for content, Chandan Sinha perform occasionally by choice not by any compulsion.\nAt young age Chandan Sinha flew from home to Mumbai ( then Bombay) to build his career as playback singer and failed , then he back home.\nMamun- a talent hunter- use the voice of Chandan Sinha for first tv serial in Bangladesh Television, BTV, Shirsho Bindu.\nWish, this might bring new crown for Chandan Sinha - the Singer of the Decade.', '2022-10-20 16:37:51', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651313/Chandan-Sinha:-singer-of-the-decade', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020singer.jpg'),
(113, 'Rezwana Choudhury Bannya receives Lifetime Achievement Award', 3, 'Prominent singer Rezwana Choudhury Bannya has received the Lifetime Achievement Award at Oikko-Channel i Music Awards 2022.\nThe award ceremony was held at Sheikh Russel Cantonment on the western side of the Padma Bridge on Tuesday night.\nBesides Rezwana Choudhury Bannya, 24 artistes and one orgranisation received the awards in 14 categories.\nComplete list of Oikko-Channel i Music Awards 2022Lifetime Achievement Award: Rezwana Choudhury BannyaModern song -- Best singer: Fahmida Nabi, Best Composer: Kishore, Best Lyricist: Asif Iqbal.\nFilm song-- Best singer: Imran Mahmudul, Best Composer: Emon Chowdhury and Best Lyricist: Mir Sabbir.', '2022-10-20 16:37:58', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651205/Rezwana-Choudhury-Bannya-receives-Lifetime-Achievement-Award', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221019Oikko-Channel_i_Music_Awards_.JPG'),
(114, 'Are soaps in danger of extinction?', 3, 'In fact, the BBC’s first radio soap opera, 1941\'s Front Line Family, did not initially air in Britain at all but in North America.\nThe US\'s first daytime TV soap opera, These Are My Children, arrived in 1949, followed by Britain\'s first TV soap opera, the BBC\'s The Grove Family, in 1954.\nUS soaps have always been a staple of daytime TV, whereas most soaps in the UK air in the evening.\nReality TV is often derided despite being one of the most influential genres of the 21st Century.\n\"Right back to the rise of Big Brother [in the early noughties], reality shows have been able to create national conversations,\" Bryan says.', '2022-10-20 16:38:17', NULL, 1, 'https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20221018-are-soaps-in-danger-of-extinction', 'httpsychef.files.bbci.co.uklive624x351p0d7szby.jpg'),
(115, 'Are soaps in danger of extinction?', 3, 'In fact, the BBC’s first radio soap opera, 1941\'s Front Line Family, did not initially air in Britain at all but in North America.\nThe US\'s first daytime TV soap opera, These Are My Children, arrived in 1949, followed by Britain\'s first TV soap opera, the BBC\'s The Grove Family, in 1954.\nUS soaps have always been a staple of daytime TV, whereas most soaps in the UK air in the evening.\nReality TV is often derided despite being one of the most influential genres of the 21st Century.\n\"Right back to the rise of Big Brother [in the early noughties], reality shows have been able to create national conversations,\" Bryan says.', '2022-10-20 16:38:35', NULL, 1, 'https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20221018-are-soaps-in-danger-of-extinction', 'httpsychef.files.bbci.co.uklive624x351p0d7szby.jpg'),
(116, 'Mills replaces injured Topley', 2, 'Scans confirmed significant ligament damage and the giant left-arm seamer was withdrawn from the squad, with fellow left-armer Tymal Mills promoted from his previous status as travelling reserve.\nA statement from the International Cricket Council (ICC) on Wednesday confirmed that Mills had been drafted into the squad.\nTopley has overcome multiple stress fractures in his back in recent years to become a key player in England\'s white-ball sides.\nSri Lankan bowler Kasun Rajitha has replaced the injured Dushmantha Chameera while all-rounder Danushka Gunathilaka will be replaced by travelling reserve Ashen Bandara, who is a batsman.\nIn the United Arab Emirates squad, travelling reserve Fahad Nawaz has replaced Zawar Farid.', '2022-10-20 16:39:08', NULL, 1, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/sports/sports-special/t20-world-cup-2022/news/mills-replaces-injured-topley-3147546', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicimages20221020reece_topley.jpg'),
(117, 'Pakistan’s T20 home series against Windies postponed', 2, 'A three-match Twenty20 series hosted by Pakistan against the West Indies in January has been postponed by mutual consent, officials said Thursday.\nThe Pakistan Cricket Board said the series will now take place in early 2024, allowing both sides to better prepare for that year\'s Twenty20 World Cup, to be held in the Caribbean and the United States.\nPakistan has largely restored its reputation as an international cricket host, with tours from Sri Lanka, South Africa, the West Indies, Australia and England in the last three years.\nThe national team was forced to play home matches on neutral venues following a militant attack on the Sri Lankan team bus in Lahore in 2009.', '2022-10-20 16:39:37', NULL, 1, 'https://www.thedailystar.net/sports/cricket/news/pakistans-t20-home-series-against-windies-postponed-3147856', 'httpsimages.thedailystar.netsitesdefaultfilesstylessocial_sharepublicimages20221020pcb_logo.jpg'),
(118, 'Prosecutors appeal Blatter, Platini acquittal in FIFA fraud trial', 2, 'Swiss prosecutors said Thursday that they had filed an appeal against the acquittal of former football chiefs Sepp Blatter and Michel Platini over a suspected fraudulent payment.\nFormer FIFA president Blatter, 86, and Platini, 67, were cleared of the allegations that shook world football and torpedoed their time at the top.\nThe Federal Criminal Court rejected the prosecution\'s request for a suspended prison sentence of a year and eight months.\nBlatter told the court the pair had actually struck a \"gentleman\'s agreement\" for Platini to be paid a million Swiss francs a year.\nBlatter was accused of misappropriation and criminal mismanagement, while Platini was accused of participating in those offences.', '2022-10-20 16:39:56', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651341/Prosecutors-appeal-Blatter-Platini-acquittal-in-FIFA-fraud-trial', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020swiss.jpg'),
(119, 'India to arrive in Bangladesh on Dec 1 for cricket series: BCB', 2, 'India\'s national cricket team is slated to arrive in Dhaka on December 1 to play a series of three ODIs and two Tests.\nThe Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) revealed the schedule on Thursday.\nIn their last tour, India played two Tests and three ODIs.\n“I thank the Board of Control for Cricket in India for working closely with the BCB in confirming the schedule.\nBangladesh played 11 Tests against India and lost nine of them with two draws.', '2022-10-20 16:40:02', NULL, 1, 'https://www.daily-sun.com/./post/651335/India-to-arrive-in-Bangladesh-on-Dec-1-for-cricket-series:-BCB', 'httpswww.daily-sun.comassetsnews_images20221020bd-ind.jpg'),
(120, 'Cristiano Ronaldo: Man Utd forward leaves Old Trafford before full-time', 2, 'Last updated on .From the section Man UtdCristiano Ronaldo\'s behaviour \'unacceptable\' - Micah RichardsManchester United forward Cristiano Ronaldo left Old Trafford before full-time in Wednesday\'s Premier League win over Tottenham.\nFormer England striker Gary Lineker said Ronaldo\'s behaviour took attention away from United\'s impressive performance against Spurs.\nRichards said Ronaldo\'s behaviour was \"disrespectful\" and he should be allowed to leave in the January transfer window.\nManny: Ronaldo walking down the tunnel instead of staying to celebrate the win with his team-mates pretty much sums his attitude up.\nHe\'ll always be a legend at Old Trafford but he needs dropping from the squad as he\'s now doing more harm than good.', '2022-10-20 16:40:20', NULL, 1, 'https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63323645', 'httpsichef.bbci.co.uklive-experiencecps624cpsprodpbAF42production_127266844_gettyimages-1244083471.jpg'),
(121, 'European Super League\'s new organiser open to English club talks', 2, 'Last updated on .From the section European FootballThere were protests from football fans and players in England about the idea of the European Super LeagueThe door is open for English clubs to join fresh talks around launching a European Super League, says a senior executive on the project.\nThe former chief executive at German broadcaster RTL has been appointed chief executive of A22 Sports Management, the company promoting a revamped Super League proposal.\nReal Madrid, Barcelona and Juventus remain wedded to the idea of a Super League.\nThey were three of 12 elite European clubs who announced the formation of the competition - which would have operated outside of Uefa\'s control - in April 2021.\nThe Super League idea could be given fresh impetus, though, with the European Court of Justice (ECJ) scheduled to rule next spring on the validity of Uefa\'s monopoly on organising cross-border competitions.', '2022-10-20 16:40:38', NULL, 1, 'https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63334283', 'httpsichef.bbci.co.uklive-experiencecps624cpsprodpbCD3Cproduction_118104525_gettyimages-1225539750.jpg');

